    <div class="container">
        <h1>Bank Fraud Complaint India – Complete Guide 2026</h1>
        <div class="meta">Updated: March 2026 | RBI Integrated Ombudsman Scheme 2026 effective from July 1</div>

        <div class="section">
            <p>If you've experienced unauthorised transactions, phishing fraud, or wrongful charges, act immediately. This guide covers every step from bank complaint to RBI Ombudsman and cyber crime reporting.</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <strong>🚨 First 3 Days are Critical:</strong> Under RBI rules, if you report fraud within 3 days, your liability is <strong>zero</strong>. After 3 days, limited liability applies.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>📞 Step 1: Immediate Action – Call 1930 (Cyber Crime Helpline)</h2>
            <p>If money was fraudulently debited, call <strong>1930</strong> immediately. This is the national cyber crime helpline.</p>
            <div class="contact-card">
                <div class="contact-item">
                    <span class="contact-label">📞 Helpline:</span>
                    <span class="contact-value"><strong>1930</strong> (24x7, toll-free)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="contact-item">
                    <span class="contact-label">🌐 Portal:</span>
                    <span class="contact-value"><a href="https://cybercrime.gov.in" target="_blank">cybercrime.gov.in</a></span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p>They will try to freeze the transaction and alert your bank. Get a <strong>reference number</strong>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>🏦 Step 2: Complain to Your Bank Immediately</h2>
            <p>Even after calling 1930, you must formally complain to your bank.</p>
            
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <div class="step-title">Call customer care</div>
                    <p>Report the transaction and get a <strong>Service Request Number (SRN)</strong>. Note the date and time.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <div class="step-title">Send email to grievance officer</div>
                    <p>Most banks have a dedicated email: <strong>grievance@[bankname].co.in</strong>. Include transaction details, amount, and screenshots.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <div class="step-title">Wait 30 days (mandatory)</div>
                    <p>You must give the bank 30 days to resolve. If unsatisfied or no response, you can escalate.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>⚖️ Step 3: RBI Ombudsman (Effective July 1, 2026 – New Scheme)</h2>
            <p>The Reserve Bank-Integrated Ombudsman Scheme (RB-IOS) 2026 launches on July 1, 2026. It simplifies filing and increases compensation limits.</p>
            
            <div class="compensation-box">
                <h3>💰 New Compensation Limits (from July 2026)</h3>
                <div class="contact-item">
                    <span class="contact-label">Actual financial loss:</span>
                    <span class="contact-value"><strong>Up to ₹30 lakh</strong></span>
                </div>
                <div class="contact-item">
                    <span class="contact-label">Mental harassment / expenses:</span>
                    <span class="contact-value"><strong>Up to ₹3 lakh</strong></span>
                </div>
                <p>No limit on the dispute amount – only the compensation is capped.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="contact-card">
                <h3>How to File</h3>
                <div class="contact-item">
                    <span class="contact-label">🌐 Online portal:</span>
                    <span class="contact-value"><a href="https://cms.rbi.org.in" target="_blank">cms.rbi.org.in</a></span>
                </div>
                <div class="contact-item">
                    <span class="contact-label">✉️ Email:</span>
                    <span class="contact-value">crpc@rbi.org.in</span>
                </div>
                <div class="contact-item">
                    <span class="contact-label">📮 Postal:</span>
                    <span class="contact-value">Centralised Receipt and Processing Centre, RBI, Chandigarh</span>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Timeline:</strong> File within 90 days after bank's final reply or 30 days of no reply.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>💳 Step 4: Chargeback (For Credit Card Frauds)</h2>
            <p>Credit cards have a global dispute mechanism called chargeback.</p>
            <div class="contact-card">
                <h3>How to Request Chargeback</h3>
                <p>Email your bank with subject: <strong>"Chargeback Request – Reason Code [CODE]"</strong></p>
                <p>Common reason codes: Visa Code 13.1 (Services Not Received), Mastercard Code 4853 (Cardholder Dispute).</p>
                <p>Burden of proof shifts to the merchant.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

